---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Glossary" description="Canonical terms used across Groundwork's API, documentation, and patterns">
  <section class="gw-section">
    <div class="gw-width gw-prose">
      <h1 class="gw-heading-l">Glossary</h1>
      <p>
        Groundwork uses a small canonical vocabulary across its API, documentation, and patterns. The terms
        below define the concepts in four groups; the section after that shows how the terms compose.
      </p>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Form controls</h2>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="field">Field</h3>
      <p>
        A labelled form control with optional hint and error. Two shapes:
        <code class="gw-mono">&lt;Field&gt;</code> (a <code class="gw-mono">&lt;div&gt;</code> +
        <code class="gw-mono">&lt;label&gt;</code> shell wrapping one control) and a
        <a class="gw-link" href="#choice-group">Choice group</a> (a
        <code class="gw-mono">&lt;fieldset&gt;</code> + <code class="gw-mono">&lt;legend&gt;</code> shell
        wrapping multiple option inputs).
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="field-consumer">Field consumer</h3>
      <p>
        The form-control element rendered inside a <a class="gw-link" href="#field">Field</a> — receives
        ARIA props from the Field and applies them. Examples: Input, Textarea, Select; for a Choice group,
        the individual radio and checkbox inputs.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="choice-group">Choice group</h3>
      <p>
        A <code class="gw-mono">&lt;fieldset&gt;</code>-backed <a class="gw-link" href="#field">Field</a> for
        picking from a short, visible list. RadioGroup (single-select) and CheckboxGroup (multi-select) are
        the two public shapes.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="field-description">Field description</h3>
      <p>
        The bundle that wires a <a class="gw-link" href="#field">Field</a>'s label,
        <a class="gw-link" href="#hint">Hint</a>, and <a class="gw-link" href="#field-error">Field error</a>
        to its <a class="gw-link" href="#field-consumer">Field consumer</a>: the derived IDs, the ARIA
        attribute bundles (input-style and fieldset-style), and the rendered hint and error nodes. Produced
        by <code class="gw-mono">describeField()</code>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="hint">Hint</h3>
      <p>
        Short supplementary copy explaining what the user should enter. Shown before the control; referenced
        by <code class="gw-mono">aria-describedby</code>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="field-error">Field error</h3>
      <p>
        Structured error copy with <code class="gw-mono">{`{ problem, fix }`}</code> — problem names what is
        wrong, fix tells the user how to correct it. Both Field and ErrorSummary format it consistently.
      </p>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Tokens</h2>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="primitive-token">Primitive token</h3>
      <p>
        A raw value on a closed scale, prefixed <code class="gw-mono">--_gw-</code>. Private — component CSS
        must not reference these directly.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="semantic-token">Semantic token</h3>
      <p>
        A public CSS custom property naming a decision
        (<code class="gw-mono">--ink-secondary</code>, <code class="gw-mono">--action</code>). References a
        <a class="gw-link" href="#primitive-token">Primitive token</a>. The only tokens component CSS is
        allowed to reference.
      </p>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Composition</h2>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="decision-area">Decision area</h3>
      <p>
        A bounded region of UI in which the user is being asked to commit to an action — a form, a dialog, a
        card, or a focused page section. At most one primary Button per Decision area; secondary and ghost
        buttons support the primary. A single page may contain multiple Decision areas, each with its own
        primary action.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="transaction">Transaction</h3>
      <p>
        A user atomically submitting structured information through the UI — all the answers committed
        together, in one UI step or across several. Small or medium transactions fit one screen; large
        transactions span sections.
      </p>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">Documentation</h2>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="pattern">Pattern</h3>
      <p>
        A reusable recipe documented in <a class="gw-link" href="/patterns/">/patterns/</a>: when to use it,
        when not to use it, and how to assemble Groundwork components to apply it. Patterns are
        usage-shaped, not component-shaped — a single pattern may compose many components, and a single
        component may participate in many patterns. Larger patterns embed a
        <a class="gw-link" href="#flow">Flow</a> as the interactive demo and test surface.
      </p>

      <h3 class="gw-heading-s" id="flow">Flow</h3>
      <p>
        A full interactive journey embedded within a <a class="gw-link" href="#pattern">Pattern</a> page:
        shows components working together in a realistic task, paired with a visible human test script and
        Playwright coverage. Not a public export — a doc and test artifact. See
        <a class="gw-link" href="/reference/conventions/flows-as-tests/">Flows as human-testable documentation</a>
        for the convention.
      </p>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">How these terms compose</h2>
      <ul class="gw-list">
        <li>
          A <a class="gw-link" href="#field">Field</a> owns one
          <a class="gw-link" href="#field-description">Field description</a>, which wires its label,
          <a class="gw-link" href="#hint">Hint</a>, and <a class="gw-link" href="#field-error">Field error</a>
          to its <a class="gw-link" href="#field-consumer">Field consumer</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          A <a class="gw-link" href="#choice-group">Choice group</a> is a
          <a class="gw-link" href="#field">Field</a> whose consumers are the choice inputs.
        </li>
        <li>
          A <a class="gw-link" href="#field-description">Field description</a> is produced by
          <code class="gw-mono">describeField(id, &#123; hint, error &#125;)</code> and consumed by both
          <code class="gw-mono">&lt;Field&gt;</code> and the Choice group module.
        </li>
        <li>
          Component CSS references <a class="gw-link" href="#semantic-token">Semantic tokens</a> only;
          Semantic tokens reference <a class="gw-link" href="#primitive-token">Primitive tokens</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          A <a class="gw-link" href="#pattern">Pattern</a> may embed one
          <a class="gw-link" href="#flow">Flow</a> as its interactive demo; small patterns may have no Flow.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="gw-heading-m">A note on the word "Field"</h2>
      <p>
        "Field" names both the domain concept (any labelled form control) and the specific
        <code class="gw-mono">&lt;Field&gt;</code> React component. Context almost always disambiguates;
        when it does not, the docs say "the Field component" or "a labelled field" to keep the two senses
        apart.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
